newsitem.title: NEW ZEALAND: NZ 43-day seasonal bills yield 9.849 pct at tender.
newsitem.headline: NZ 43-day seasonal bills yield 9.849 pct at tender.

text.p: The weighted average yield on NZ$100 million of 43-day seasonal Treasury bills at Tuesday's tender was 9.849 percent, the Reserve Bank said.
The bank rejected bids for NZ$100 million of a similar maturity at last week's tender.
The average yield for NZ$100 million of 119-day bills was 9.715 percent on bids of $379 million.
The average yield for $100 million of 135-day bills was 9.686 percent, with $394 million in bids.

Last week, $100 million of 104-day seasonal bills yielded 9.675 percent on bids of $530 million, while $100 million of 126-day seasonal bills yielded 9.639 percent, with $405 million of bids submitted.
